<h2> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes_for_Week_3:_6.1._Could_we_reduce_the_shortage_of_human_organs.3F">Notes for Week 3: 6.1. Could we reduce the shortage of human organs?</span></h2>
<p><a href="/wiki/images/a/a5/6.1_Could_We_Reduce_the_shortage_of_human_organs.jpg" class="image"><img alt="6.1 Could We Reduce the shortage of human organs.jpg" src="/wiki/images/a/a5/6.1_Could_We_Reduce_the_shortage_of_human_organs.jpg" width="959" height="542" /></a></p>
<p>Every time we create an incentive for people to donate organs, we are moving the point towards the equilibrium.
<ul><li> Such as marking a box in a driver's license</p>
</li></ul>

<p>Notice that the surplus for society increases as the point is moved towards the right.  Before we only had surplus of A and B, but as the point moves right, we now have C and D too.</p>
<p></p>

